sort of an assistant.

00:16:13.532 --> 00:16:14.806
He wouldn't say that now,

00:16:14.806 --> 00:16:16.975
(audience laughs)
but because he was younger

00:16:16.975 --> 00:16:20.142
and I've known George Lucas
throughout all of his career.

00:16:20.142 --> 00:16:23.982
Produced his first movies like THX 1138

00:16:23.982 --> 00:16:27.110
and American Graffiti before he went

00:16:27.110 --> 00:16:31.393
off on his own to do the
astonishing work that he did

00:16:31.393 --> 00:16:32.468
and he's remained my friend.

00:16:32.468 --> 00:16:34.405
He's one of the few directors who still

00:16:34.405 --> 00:16:36.374
lives more or less in Northern California.

00:16:36.374 --> 00:16:39.011
I think Solomon knows him.

00:16:39.011 --> 00:16:40.330
(Interviewer laughs)
(audience laughs)

00:16:40.330 --> 00:16:41.326
Did I answer your question?

00:16:41.326 --> 00:16:43.290
(audience laughs)
- No, absolutely,

00:16:43.290 --> 00:16:44.445
but just following up on George

00:16:44.445 --> 00:16:46.757
