because there's a philosophy that believes

00:20:02.470 --> 00:20:07.146
that music is the only way
that we can really understand

00:20:07.146 --> 00:20:10.455
what's really out there,
beyond our senses.

00:20:10.455 --> 00:20:13.561
Any rate, so learning, I always thought

00:20:13.561 --> 00:20:14.568
when I was a little kid,

00:20:14.568 --> 00:20:16.456
if they said to me, "You know, Francis,

00:20:16.456 --> 00:20:19.453
"you're about to learn
about this and about that

00:20:19.453 --> 00:20:21.203
"and you're gonna learn about algebra

00:20:21.203 --> 00:20:23.236
"and algebra comes from the Arabs.

00:20:23.236 --> 00:20:25.032
"It was called al jabr

00:20:25.032 --> 00:20:26.903
"and they probably
learned it from the Greeks

00:20:26.903 --> 00:20:29.246
"and it's really an
exciting way to solve."

