and that a lot of it focuses
on the Middle East and Islam,

00:21:44.762 --> 00:21:46.909
but no one knows that
really you have to go back

00:21:46.909 --> 00:21:50.473
almost to the first
World War to understand

00:21:50.473 --> 00:21:55.039
the bad feelings that were
engendered at that time

00:21:55.039 --> 00:21:59.039
and also that Islam is
not, Islam was the zenith

00:22:01.274 --> 00:22:05.441
of intellectual study and
science in the 13th century,

00:22:08.390 --> 00:22:10.350
in terms of, well, it's interesting

00:22:10.350 --> 00:22:13.560
'cause in Islam, you have
to pray five times a day

00:22:13.560 --> 00:22:17.900
and you have to point when
you pray towards Mecca.

00:22:17.900 --> 00:22:22.299
So it was to their advantage
to really understand time

00:22:22.299 --> 00:22:25.761
so they knew they would pray
at the right time each day.

00:22:25.761 --> 00:22:29.381
So they studied the heavens
to be masters of time

00:22:29.381 --> 00:22:33.047
and the reason that Islamic
science knew so much

00:22:33.047 --> 00:22:37.385
about the heavens and
time was for that reason.

00:22:37.385 --> 00:22:39.776
It's because they, and they wanted to

00:22:39.776 --> 00:22:41.213
point in the right direction,

00:22:41.213 --> 00:22:43.372
so they brought so much to us

00:22:43.372 --> 00:22:46.955
in these areas of
astronomy and navigation.

00:22:48.962 --> 00:22:53.129
Of course Islam, those states
were close to Ancient Greece,

00:22:54.068 --> 00:22:56.076
so they preserved a lot of the knowledge

00:22:56.076 --> 00:22:58.080
that had been in Greek and that's how

00:22:58.080 --> 00:23:01.163
we still have such things as algebra.

